The paper discusses a framework for implementing differentially private algorithms, which is relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the design and architecture of the Ektelo system, which involves topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT).
